dpkg tool
---------
debian package tool

.deb
-----
man 5 deb 
The .deb format is the Debian binary package file format. It is understood since dpkg 0.93.76, and is generated by default since dpkg 1.2.0 and 1.1.1elf (i386/ELF builds).


environment
------------
$ mkdir -p ~/build-deb/try/DEBIAN
$ cd ~/build-deb
$ vi try/DEBIAN/control
Package: try
Version: 0.1
Architecture: all
Description: This is a test package.
Maintainer: developer <jedy.wei@advantech.com.tw>

NOTE:  debian version scheme
        [epoch:]upstrem_version[-debian_revision] 
        2.2.6-1

       architecture : amd64

$ cat /var/lib/dpkg/available   to get a control file example 

build and command
------------------
dpkg or dpkg-deb command

$ dpkg --build try          // -b

$ dpkg --info try.deb       // -I

$ dpkg --field try.deb      // -f

$ dpkg --contents try.deb   // -c



test 
----
$ sudo dpkg -i try.deb      // --install
$ dpkg -l try               // --list
$ dpkg -s try               // --status
$ dpkg -L try               // --listfiles 
